He was leading a university-sponsored
research expedition in a remote section

19:47.105 --> 19:51.101
of the peruvian jungle Yomuibato?

19:51.305 --> 19:53.500
And that's where he died.

19:53.606 --> 19:55.101
Sad.

19:55.208 --> 19:56.901
He had a real passion for what he did.

19:57.007 --> 19:58.001
Yeah.

19:58.106 --> 20:00.202
Anyway, I think he's got
an issue with dr. Grogan.

20:00.308 --> 20:01.902
Ever since she got back
from the expedition,

20:02.005 --> 20:04.501
she's been getting the credit
for all their discoveries.

20:04.607 --> 20:07.103
Hey, does Grogan know
that she's with ghost?

20:07.206 --> 20:08.602
Well, I think she knows
that something's wrong.

20:08.707 --> 20:10.501
I just don't think
she knows it's him.

20:10.608 --> 20:13.300
I guess somebody's got to tell her.

20:13.405 --> 20:14.203
You?

20:14.305 --> 20:17.803
No. This is me going to work,
although I could call her.

20:17.907 --> 20:20.201
And say, "dr. Grogan, you know
you've got a ghost attached to you,"

20:20.307 --> 20:21.701
and then hang up real quickly.

20:21.805 --> 20:24.503
That's a great idea.
Maybe I'll try that.

20:24.605 --> 20:26.300
- Love you.
- I love you, too.

20:26.405 --> 20:27.800
I'll try not to wake you up.

20:27.906 --> 20:30.502
Please do.

20:30.708 --> 20:34.301
I like to know you're back.

20:37.607 --> 20:40.300
Ok, Martin.

21:10.805 --> 21:13.800
Honey! I'm home!

21:50.907 --> 21:53.502
Who is it?

22:04.705 --> 22:06.001
You saw me!

22:06.106 --> 22:08.102
You saw me!
There's no denying you saw me!

22:08.208 --> 22:11.903
Now open up!
We need to talk!

22:13.206 --> 22:15.000
- Hi.
- You've been drinking.

22:15.106 --> 22:17.403
- Statement or question?
- What do you want?

22:17.505 --> 22:19.601
What do I want?
Good.

22:19.705 --> 22:22.700
I'll tell you what I want.

22:22.805 --> 22:24.703
I want to know...

22:24.808 --> 22:27.403
I want to know what it is that you do.

22:27.505 --> 22:28.800
You shouldn't be doing this.

22:28.907 --> 22:32.803
The world is filled with people
doing things they shouldn't be doing.

22:32.908 --> 22:35.200
Having sex with other people's wives, 

22:35.307 --> 22:37.900
cheating on their taxes,

22:38.005 --> 22:41.303
running red lights...

22:41.806 --> 22:44.101
Iraq.

22:44.305 --> 22:46.202
What's your deal, lady?

22:46.307 --> 22:51.202
What is going on? You come to me with
this Romano character and his hat,

22:51.307 --> 22:55.601
and then you start drawing me pictures.
Not very good pictures, I might add

22:55.705 --> 22:58.601
and the next thing you know,
things are going bump in the night,

22:58.705 --> 23:01.801
and  I'm not a bump-in-the-night
type of guy.

23:01.907 --> 23:03.201
I don't get it.

23:03.305 --> 23:07.601
You draw me symbols, numbers, music...

23:10.806 --> 23:12.602
How long have you lived here?

23:12.706 --> 23:14.201
Almost two years.

23:14.408 --> 23:17.200
That's good. That was a test.
You passed.

23:17.306 --> 23:21.601
Get the easy question out of the way
before I ask the hard one.

23:21.707 --> 23:23.003
Good for you.

23:23.105 --> 23:25.502
I guess your husband's not home,

23:25.607 --> 23:30.000
because if he was, I'd probably
be pulling his fist out of my face
right about now.

23:30.107 --> 23:32.901
You might get to do that
at a later date.

23:33.007 --> 23:35.300
Well, that's the really good thing
about being too drunk,

23:35.406 --> 23:38.401
because you have a false sense
of invulnerability.

23:38.505 --> 23:40.502
Yeah, well, eventually,
it wears off.

23:40.606 --> 23:43.400
So let's get started.

23:43.507 --> 23:46.103
This isn't about a book
you guys are writing.

23:46.208 --> 23:47.901
You're not writing a book,
Melinda Gordon.

23:48.008 --> 23:49.303
You're not writing a book.

23:49.408 --> 23:52.502
You got something inside of you.

23:52.607 --> 23:55.602
Something special inside of you.

23:55.705 --> 23:59.701
That store that you got down there,
that's not what you're about.

23:59.805 --> 24:01.800
No.

24:01.907 --> 24:05.600
That's a front
for what's inside of you.

24:05.706 --> 24:10.803
And I don't know, you could say it is
or not true, and it won't matter to me

24:10.907 --> 24:12.303
because I know it's true.

24:12.407 --> 24:14.503
Ok. Well, if you know it's true,
then why don't you go home?

24:14.605 --> 24:17.100
Because I don't even know
what I know anymore.

24:17.206 --> 24:21.402
- That doesn't make any sense.
- I know.

24:21.505 --> 24:25.400
That's why I'm here,
trying to make sense of something.

24:25.507 --> 24:29.702
I'm trying to make sense of anything.

24:35.106 --> 24:36.600
Why are you interested in jungle plants?

24:36.706 --> 24:38.700
No, forget that.
I don't care about jungle plants,

24:38.806 --> 24:41.703
and I don't think you care
about jungle plants, either.

24:41.805 --> 24:44.301
Suddenly you want to know
about my kanaima manikin

24:44.408 --> 24:47.803
and how does dr. Grogan

24:48.405 --> 24:49.902
figure into all this?

24:50.006 --> 24:52.201
Yeah, I really don't want to talk
to you when you're like this.

24:52.306 --> 24:56.702
I may be drunk, Melinda Gordon,
but at least...

24:56.808 --> 24:59.702
I'm telling the truth.

24:59.808 --> 25:02.900
I'm gonna cut to the chase, ok?

25:03.007 --> 25:04.302
I'm just gonna come right out
and say it.

25:04.406 --> 25:07.601
I don't think there's enough
give and take between you and I
in this relationship.

25:07.706 --> 25:12.901
So I think we'd better cut it off
before it gets too serious.

25:13.007 --> 25:15.300
Yeah. I said that.

25:15.407 --> 25:16.703
Besides, whatever it is you're doing,

25:16.808 --> 25:20.303
I'm sure it's probably
just smoke and mirrors.

25:20.407 --> 25:25.001
Next, you'll just pull
a rabbit out of your hat.

25:25.106 --> 25:26.700
Full circle.

25:26.807 --> 25:29.603
Back to the hat.

25:29.705 --> 25:32.901
I never really looked good in hats.

25:33.005 --> 25:35.702
But with your hat, there's
a very interesting question,

25:35.807 --> 25:38.301
and that's whether or not will
the rabbit be dead or alive.

25:38.405 --> 25:40.000
I should call you a cab.

25:40.108 --> 25:42.600
Now, that's a good idea!

25:42.708 --> 25:44.800
Call the professor a cab.

25:44.905 --> 25:46.902
Ah, too bad I won't be in it.

25:47.006 --> 25:49.903
I will see you again...

25:50.007 --> 25:52.400
never.

25:56.905 --> 26:00.100
Damn it!

26:00.108 --> 26:02.101
What is wrong with you?

26:02.206 --> 26:05.500
I can't find my keys.

26:05.806 --> 26:07.002
You got my keys!

26:07.106 --> 26:09.703
You took them when you grabbed my arm,
and you took my keys.

26:09.806 --> 26:12.901
Now give them back.

26:13.905 --> 26:17.301
Please go to Grogan now.

26:18.805 --> 26:21.900
Are you all right?

26:22.006 --> 26:24.302
What the hell just happened?

26:24.408 --> 26:26.200
Where does dr. Grogan live?

26:26.307 --> 26:30.602
- What?
- Do you know where she lives?

26:38.506 --> 26:40.600
Why are we going to dr. Grogan's house?

26:40.708 --> 26:42.201
We'll find out when we get there.

26:42.305 --> 26:44.601
If you think something's wrong,
tell me.

26:44.708 --> 26:46.001
You told me.

26:46.105 --> 26:49.201
Look at the blood.

26:50.307 --> 26:52.401
I should get to a hospital, I think.

26:52.505 --> 26:55.301
It's not yours.

26:55.407 --> 27:00.202
Why does that not make me
feel one bit better?

27:03.808 --> 27:07.002
Maybe she's not home.

27:07.105 --> 27:09.400
Something's going on in this house.

27:09.505 --> 27:12.500
Are you serious?

27:17.806 --> 27:21.303
She's inside.
Break down the door.

27:21.405 --> 27:23.302
- Do you want me to do it?
- Yes!

27:23.405 --> 27:24.601
Fine.

27:24.705 --> 27:27.301
No, no, no, no, no, no!
I'll do it.

27:27.408 --> 27:31.603
Come on. I'll do it.
Back up, please.

27:43.207 --> 27:44.502
I killed him.

27:44.607 --> 27:46.803
Oh, my god.

27:46.906 --> 27:48.801
I killed martin.

27:48.905 --> 27:51.702
I killed him.

27:55.008 --> 27:57.503
Call 911!

27:58.107 --> 28:00.601
It's ok.

28:02.507 --> 28:04.502
We just tried to keep her walking
until you got here.

28:04.607 --> 28:08.402
Well, you did the right thing.

28:08.707 --> 28:11.401
Did Payne have something
to do with this? Or her?

28:11.505 --> 28:15.200
No. It was an anonymous tip.

28:16.508 --> 28:19.503
Fill me in later.

28:20.105 --> 28:22.302
Hey, I could really use a ride home.

28:22.408 --> 28:23.602
Your car's at my house.

28:23.706 --> 28:28.000
Well, it's not going anywhere.
No keys.

28:41.007 --> 28:42.900
That was an interesting evening, huh?

28:43.008 --> 28:45.300
Yeah.

28:45.508 --> 28:47.801
So...

28:49.406 --> 28:51.603
look, if I ask, will you tell me?

28:51.706 --> 28:52.602
How I knew?

28:52.708 --> 28:56.503
Among other things I can't blame on
my overindulgence in alcohol, yes.

28:56.607 --> 28:59.000
I just wish I knew what
your reaction was gonna be.

28:59.105 --> 29:05.103
It'll probably be a high level
of incredulity, but I'll try
to keep it within reason.

29:05.206 --> 29:07.801
If I'm gonna say it,
I'm gonna need you to promise

29:07.905 --> 29:10.600
because it's not something
I want everyone to know.

29:10.706 --> 29:13.302
I... I won't tell anyone.
Do you want the cross-my-heart routine?

29:13.407 --> 29:14.502
You got it.

29:14.605 --> 29:18.100
No. A simple promise will be good.

29:18.208 --> 29:24.602
I promise you, Melinda,
whatever you tell me in this car
doesn't leave this car ever.

29:24.707 --> 29:28.203
I can speak to and see...

29:30.508 --> 29:31.902
Is this fill in the blank?

29:32.008 --> 29:33.602
The dead.

29:33.708 --> 29:34.803
You don't mean the grateful, do you?

29:34.907 --> 29:38.002
That's how I knew that
dr. Grogan was in trouble.

29:38.107 --> 29:41.801
Martin Schaer. He used you
to tell me to get to her.

29:41.905 --> 29:44.102
It's his spirit that you felt.
That's why you had blood your mouth.

29:44.207 --> 29:47.902
Because he did when he died.

29:48.705 --> 29:51.901
Now you know. Happy?

29:52.906 --> 29:55.403
I don't if "happy" is the right word.

29:55.508 --> 29:57.103
Does this happen a lot?

29:57.208 --> 30:00.001
It's not something
I want to go into right now.

30:00.107 --> 30:05.301
Look, you can believe me or not,
and if you can find another way
to explain what happened tonight,

30:05.408 --> 30:08.302
it's ok with me.

30:08.405 --> 30:11.500
I wish you could hear the argument
I'm having with myself in my head
right now.

30:11.605 --> 30:14.801
Is that why you came to my house?

30:14.908 --> 30:15.701
Yes.

30:15.805 --> 30:17.902
Was it necessary to be drunk?

30:18.005 --> 30:25.202
Yes, because I didn't decide
to come to your house until after
I had started drinking.

30:28.405 --> 30:31.701
I want to go home now.

31:21.007 --> 31:23.202
Oh... no.

31:23.307 --> 31:25.902
Not again.

31:28.908 --> 31:31.700
This is where I found it.

31:31.806 --> 31:35.702
I had to be part of a ceremony
with the Machiguenga.

31:35.806 --> 31:41.201
A ritual, so they would take me
to a place they considered sacred.

31:41.307 --> 31:43.402
I wanted to find the plant
that they told me about.

31:43.508 --> 31:44.901
Una de gato,

31:45.005 --> 31:46.500
The cat's claw.

31:46.606 --> 31:52.501
The Machiguenga were very protective.
They'd only take two of us.

31:53.808 --> 31:55.402
Where have you been?

31:55.506 --> 31:59.100
With my new best friends,
the Machiguenga.

31:59.207 --> 32:04.302
- Can those guys party or what?
- Will they take us?

32:05.808 --> 32:08.700
- Yes, but just two.
- Is that a good idea?

32:08.805 --> 32:10.803
It's their jungle, their rules.
I'd go by myself if that's what they...

32:10.906 --> 32:14.302
Ok, ok. So you and who?

32:15.806 --> 32:18.600
Gee, I wonder.

32:23.805 --> 32:25.702
What have you been drinking?

32:25.808 --> 32:27.202
I'm really not sure.

32:27.305 --> 32:28.201
You don't know what you drank?

32:28.305 --> 32:33.501
It was a machiguenga cerenial concoction.
I had to drink it to seal the deal.

32:33.606 --> 32:37.102
I have no idea what was in it, but I'm
positive it wouldn't get FDA approval.

32:37.207 --> 32:41.703
It tasted just you know, pine tar
and a little hint of bat urine.

32:41.805 --> 32:43.302
Oh, that's nice. That's romantic.

32:43.406 --> 32:44.900
Actually, it was.

32:45.005 --> 32:46.900
I had...

32:47.008 --> 32:52.603
I had the most incredible visions,
all of them involving you.

32:52.706 --> 32:56.800
And they swore to me
that it would increase sexual...

32:56.908 --> 32:59.201
Ok, ok, ok. Fine, fine.

32:59.307 --> 33:02.302
So when do we go?

33:03.106 --> 33:05.501
3 hours.

33:05.608 --> 33:08.601
And apparently it's quite a hike.

33:08.705 --> 33:12.503
- Is that ok with you?
- Yeah.

33:13.807 --> 33:15.903
You're a little hot.
Do you feel ok?

33:16.006 --> 33:20.102
Oh, yeah. If I'm hot,
it's just because I'm here with you.

33:20.208 --> 33:22.600
- I'm telling you, those visions...
- Hey, I'm not kidding.

33:22.705 --> 33:27.702
- I think you've got a fever.
- What? Oh. I mean, come on.

33:27.806 --> 33:28.800
A little temperature?

33:28.907 --> 33:30.400
That's not gonna keep me
from going there,

33:30.505 --> 33:33.403
especially after drinking what
I had to drink to make it happen.

33:33.507 --> 33:36.503
If the Machiguenga think that I'm a wimp,
it's gonna blow the whole deal.

33:36.606 --> 33:37.801
Come on. We go.

33:37.905 --> 33:38.701
We're going.

33:38.808 --> 33:42.100
We go no matter what.

33:42.806 --> 33:46.501
Hey, I'll take two aspirins,
and call you in the morning.

33:46.605 --> 33:49.003
All right? If I can find a phone
that works in the Yomuibato.

33:49.108 --> 33:51.403
Call.

33:59.505 --> 34:01.903
Sorry!

34:24.806 --> 34:26.000
How's dr. Grogan?

34:26.105 --> 34:28.000
We got in there just in time.

34:28.108 --> 34:32.701
They pumped her stomach immediately,
but they still don't know what she took.

34:32.804 --> 34:35.502
You saved her life, you know.

34:35.608 --> 34:38.601
You know, people get awards from
the mayor for doing that sort of thing.

34:38.706 --> 34:42.501
I'd have to share mine with a ghost.
He told me.

34:42.606 --> 34:46.801
Tell me, what was
Payne doing there?

34:47.405 --> 34:49.800
I told him.

34:49.906 --> 34:51.400
Wow.

34:51.507 --> 34:55.703
I think my ghosts are starting
to invade his life.

34:55.806 --> 34:56.702
Did he say that?

34:56.808 --> 34:59.001
No, not exactly.

34:59.106 --> 35:01.302
But he knows
that things are happening,

35:01.408 --> 35:06.800
and I couldn't come up with
a rational explanation, so...

35:07.208 --> 35:09.403
I run out of lies sometimes.

35:09.508 --> 35:11.802
Hey, they're not lies.

35:11.908 --> 35:16.802
I mean, whatever you think,
but they're not lies.

35:18.407 --> 35:22.602
He probably didn't believe me anyway.

35:23.308 --> 35:26.300
- Now you're here, I can sleep.
- That's right.

35:26.406 --> 35:28.803
Well...

35:31.205 --> 35:34.100
Melinda Gordon?

35:34.908 --> 35:37.600
Wow. I mean, yeah.

35:37.705 --> 35:40.803
Sorry to just show up like this.

35:40.905 --> 35:43.401
Rick came to see me in the hospital.

35:43.508 --> 35:46.600
Uh, sorry.
Professor Payne.

35:46.707 --> 35:49.100
He told me how you found me.

35:49.208 --> 35:50.800
He did?

35:50.908 --> 35:53.203
Yeah.

35:53.905 --> 35:57.500
He said you saved my life.

35:58.006 --> 35:58.903
Yeah.

35:59.005 --> 36:02.600
Um, do you want to come in?

36:07.606 --> 36:11.500
Uh, Rick said he was with you...

36:13.108 --> 36:16.703
That you knew I was in trouble?

36:16.808 --> 36:20.402
And he said you knew things
about Martin Schaer.

36:20.507 --> 36:23.201
He said he couldn't tell me
what you knew, just...

36:23.308 --> 36:26.302
I had to ask you.

36:27.605 --> 36:29.902
Did... did you know Martin?

36:30.008 --> 36:31.702
I know him, yes.

36:31.807 --> 36:35.303
You were with him when he died.

36:35.406 --> 36:38.400
It was my fault.

36:40.407 --> 36:43.601
I knew he was sick.
I should have kept him from going.

36:43.708 --> 36:47.301
Do you think you could have?

36:47.405 --> 36:50.701
You don't understand.

36:51.906 --> 36:54.602
I left him.

36:55.308 --> 36:58.001
I left him.

37:01.405 --> 37:03.202
The guards were moving too fast.

37:03.307 --> 37:04.802
I can't see where they went.

37:04.905 --> 37:08.002
Marty, I see some.

37:08.308 --> 37:10.803
It's right here.
We found it.

37:10.906 --> 37:12.900
Marty, are you ok?

37:13.008 --> 37:14.401
Marty.

37:14.508 --> 37:16.101
Uh! Ok. Marty.

37:16.208 --> 37:17.102
Come on.

37:17.207 --> 37:18.700
We can't stop here.

37:18.807 --> 37:20.302
Wait. Wait.

37:20.406 --> 37:23.303
No. No.
We're going back.

37:23.407 --> 37:25.600
Ok.

37:25.708 --> 37:28.502
Penn, it's ok. I'm ok.
It's ok. I just--

37:28.607 --> 37:29.800
We have to go back.

37:29.907 --> 37:33.702
- This is the only time we can do this.
- No. No. We have to go back.

37:33.806 --> 37:36.800
Will you hold...

37:38.806 --> 37:41.200
I want you to go.

37:41.307 --> 37:43.001
Go back the way we came.

37:43.107 --> 37:46.001
I'll wait here.

37:49.706 --> 37:53.000
I love you.

37:53.007 --> 37:56.901
I'll be here when you get back.

37:57.408 --> 37:59.602
Ok.

37:59.906 --> 38:02.402
I'll go back. I'll bring help.

38:02.506 --> 38:04.400
I'll promise.

38:04.505 --> 38:06.001
I went back to camp as fast as I could,

38:06.105 --> 38:11.100
but he wasn't where I'd left him
when we got back.

38:11.705 --> 38:15.603
We looked for him for two days.

38:19.908 --> 38:24.803
We were supposed to get married
when we got back.

38:25.507 --> 38:27.900
When I got back, I...

38:28.007 --> 38:29.901
I was so empty inside,

38:30.007 --> 38:31.302
all I could do was work.

38:31.408 --> 38:36.202
I couldn't stop to think. If I did,
I would think of him, and...

38:36.306 --> 38:42.501
and then I was getting all the credit
for things that we did together.

38:42.905 --> 38:47.502
I couldn't have done
any of it without him.

38:47.905 --> 38:50.403
And the university
insisted it was ok.

38:50.506 --> 38:55.002
The more famous the professor,
the more grant money for the university.

38:55.105 --> 38:59.502
He was sick for 3 days
before you left him.

38:59.606 --> 39:02.602
How do you know that?

39:02.707 --> 39:04.403
I've seen Martin.

39:04.505 --> 39:07.202
His spirit.

39:07.308 --> 39:09.800
He's here with us right now.

39:09.905 --> 39:11.100
I...

39:11.208 --> 39:13.402
I don't believe you.

39:13.506 --> 39:15.402
I didn't want to believe I was sick.

39:15.508 --> 39:18.803
There was so much work we had to do,
and there wasn't enough time to do it.

39:18.906 --> 39:22.303
He didn't want to say anything
about being sick because

39:22.405 --> 39:24.101
there was so much work
you had to do.

39:24.206 --> 39:26.801
And now she blames herself for
what happened, but there's nothing

39:26.905 --> 39:30.600
that could have saved me. It was
dengue fever. Mosquitoes carry it.

39:30.708 --> 39:33.003
He knows that you blame yourself,

39:33.107 --> 39:34.801
but he was already dying.

39:34.906 --> 39:36.601
He had dengue fever.

39:36.705 --> 39:43.400
I tried to make it back on my own,
but I wasn't thinking right,
and I got lost.

39:51.707 --> 39:54.903
I couldn't find her.

39:56.108 --> 39:59.501
When I finally couldn't walk anymore,
I just...

39:59.607 --> 40:02.703
I lay down to die.

40:03.605 --> 40:06.200
But I thought that...

40:06.307 --> 40:09.702
no matter what happened,

40:10.108 --> 40:13.501
I would always love her.

40:14.608 --> 40:18.301
He was thinking of you
when he died.

40:18.407 --> 40:22.703
He knew that he would
always love you.

40:24.207 --> 40:27.602
I'm so lost without you.

40:28.905 --> 40:30.800
Everywhere I go,

40:30.908 --> 40:32.803
everywhere I look,

40:32.908 --> 40:35.303
I can feel you.

40:35.406 --> 40:37.501
Us.

40:37.607 --> 40:41.101
You showed me everything.

40:41.508 --> 40:42.903
And now I don't want...

40:43.005 --> 40:47.203
I don't want to be here
without you.

40:48.905 --> 40:51.102
Please don't leave me.

40:51.207 --> 40:52.300
We were meant to be together.

40:52.407 --> 40:55.903
We were meant to show each other
the things we did, to teach each other,

40:56.005 --> 40:58.600
and now it's...
it's meant to be different.

40:58.707 --> 41:01.801
But nothing...
nothing can take it away.

41:01.905 --> 41:07.200
We'll both bring all of it
with us wherever we go next.

41:07.906 --> 41:10.500
I'll tell her.

41:10.606 --> 41:12.603
Tell her to keep working.

41:12.705 --> 41:14.300
But tell her she's got to
keep living, too,

41:14.408 --> 41:18.800
because one's no good
without the other.

41:20.705 --> 41:22.503
It's gonna be hard for him.

41:22.607 --> 41:23.802
Who?

41:23.906 --> 41:26.000
Rick Payne.

41:26.106 --> 41:29.401
It's gonna be hard for him
to stay so cynical now.

41:29.506 --> 41:32.500
He'll find a way.

41:42.907 --> 41:46.602
What is it?
What's happening?

41:47.805 --> 41:50.000
He's crossed over.

41:50.108 --> 41:52.703
He's gone.

41:57.306 --> 41:59.002
That's a good thing, right?

41:59.107 --> 42:02.500
Yeah, it's a good thing.

42:03.406 --> 42:04.401
Come on.

42:04.508 --> 42:09.203
Let's take a walk,
and we can talk some more.

42:37.507 --> 42:39.302
I had to come back and get my car.

42:39.406 --> 42:42.302
Find your keys?

42:44.206 --> 42:47.401
Martin crossed over.

42:48.707 --> 42:50.001
- He told me...
- Hold on.

42:50.106 --> 42:56.702
I need a moment to keep my knee-jerk
cynical reaction from ignoring
all other possibilities.

42:56.807 --> 42:58.801
Ok.

42:58.905 --> 43:00.202
Martin told you...

43:00.307 --> 43:03.201
That he was worried about you.

43:03.308 --> 43:06.902
He doesn't know how you're going to
be able to stay so cynical now.

43:07.007 --> 43:08.503
I'll find a way.

43:08.605 --> 43:11.101
Exactly.

43:14.807 --> 43:18.302
I think I might have been partially
inebriated the other night.

43:18.408 --> 43:19.602
Partially.

43:19.705 --> 43:24.702
Partially, which I probably
owe you an apology for,

43:24.806 --> 43:28.403
which will come
in the very near future.

43:28.507 --> 43:31.002
No rush.

